The '''Fugang Fishery Harbor''' ({{zh|c=富岡漁港|p=Fùgāng Yúgǎng}}) is a [[harbor]] in [[Taitung City]], [[Taitung County]], [[Taiwan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tour.taitung.gov.tw/en-us/Travel/ScenicSpot/593/Fugang-Fish-Harbor |title=Fugang Fish Harbor |publisher=Tour.taitung.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref><ref>http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/front/photo/2015/08/08/2008120527</ref>

==Geography==
The harbor is located at Beinan Creek.

==Economy==
The harbor is the portal for sea fishing and acts as a tourist fish market.

==Destinations==
Through its jetties, it serves as the gateway access to Taiwan offshore islands:<ref name="taitung1">{{cite web|url=http://tour.taitung.gov.tw/en-us/Traffic/Island |title=Taitung Islands Transportation |publisher=Tour.taitung.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>
* [[Green Island, Taiwan|Green Island]] at [[Nanliao Harbor]]
* [[Orchid Island]] at [[Kaiyun Harbor]]

==Transportation==
The harbor is accessible by shuttle service, bus, or taxi from [[Taitung Station]].<ref name="taitung1"/>

==See also==
* [[Taitung City]]

